## 8. EXECUTION WORKFLOW

### Phase 0: Environmental Sanity Check
```bash
npm run type-check  # Must pass
npm run lint        # Must pass  
npm run test:quick  # Must pass
git status          # Must be clean
```

### Phase 1: Execute Sub-Task
- Work on single isolated task (< 2 hours)
- No looking ahead, no scope creep

### Phase 2: Verify
- Deterministic proof required
- "Looks good" = NOT verification
- Measurable output = VERIFICATION

### Phase 3: Commit
```bash
git add .
git commit -m "[Agent] Verified completion: {Task Name}"
```

### Phase 4: Handoff
- Autonomous mode: Next sub-task
- Blind mode: Output logs, await instruction

